    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\nAfer merging https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/29708, when we use LoRA on an FP8 MoE model, the following error is thrown\n```shell\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/worker_manager.py\", line 214, in create_lora_manager\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     lora_manager = create_lora_manager(\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/models.py\", line 894, in create_lora_manager\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     lora_manager = lora_manager_cls(\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/models.py\", line 813, in __init__\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     super().__init__(\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/models.py\", line 349, in __init__\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     self._create_lora_modules()\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/models.py\", line 528, in _create_lora_modules\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     from_layer(\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/utils.py\", line 93, in from_layer\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     instance_layer = lora_cls(layer)\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/layers/fused_moe.py\", line 57, in __init__\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     self._inject_lora_into_fused_moe()\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]   File \"/root/Code/vllm_dev/vllm/vllm/lora/layers/fused_moe.py\", line 140, in _inject_lora_into_fused_moe\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]     assert isinstance(\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750]            ^^^^^^^^^^^\nERROR 12-04 01:53:48 [multiproc_executor.py:750] AssertionError\n```\n\nThe reason is that when LoRA is enabled, the FP8 MoE backend is not correctly selected. \n\nThis PR fixes this issue. The reason this error wasn't thrown before is because when not using MXFP4, we always used the `modular_triton_fused_moe` to select the MOE backend.\n## Test Plan\n\n## Test Result\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
